title: Lilian Jackson Braun
description:
"The Cat Who..." is a series of mystery novels written by Lilian Jackson Braun. The books feature a reporter named Jim Qwilleran (Qwill to most) and his Siamese cats: Kao K'o-Kung (Koko for short) and Yum-Yum. Qwill uses his experience as a reporter, and Koko's suspected ESP, to help solve mysteries that the authorities can't figure out.

This is the (essentially) complete collection of Lilian Jackson Braun's wonderful "The Cat Who" series of mystery books! The unfinished, never-published 30th book, "The Cat Who Smelled Smoke," and "The Private Life of the Cat Who ...: Tales of Koko and Yum Yum (from the Journals of James Mackintosh Qwilleran)," which is mostly just excerpts from earlier books, are all that are missing. Likewise, the five related books by other authors ("The Cat Who...Companion," "The Cat Who... Quiz Book," "The Cat Who... Cookbook," "The Cat Who... Reunion Cookbook" and ""The Cat Who Killed Lilian Jackson Braun") are not included.
